%section#about.slide{'data-background-hue' => '120'}
  %h1
    about me
  %p.then
    My full name is Alexander Flatscher and I live in Austria. I started (web-) pro&shy;gramming at the age of 16 with Java&shy;Script (and HTML table lay&shy;outs... how foolish...). Now I've made my Bachelor of Science in Multi Media Tech&shy;nology with focus on web and comm&shy;unities at the Uni&shy;versity of Applied Sciences in Salzburg.
  %p.now
    Right now I mainly focus on devel&shy;oping web&shy;sites and webapps with Ruby on Rails and Java&shy;Script (with a Coffe&shy;Script flavor), al&shy;though I know some other languages too, e.g. PHP, C++, Java (Android).
  %p.like
    In the web I like to animate objects and move things around. I like fancy and colorful designs and web&shy;sites with clear edges. 

%section#work.slide{'data-background-hue' => '52'}
  %h1
    my work
  - data.works.each do |w|
    %article.item
      .image
        = image_tag "work/#{w.name.gsub(/[\s']/, ' ' => '_', '\'' => '').downcase}.png"
      .info
        %h2
          = w.name
        %p.categories
          - w.categories.each do |c|
            = (c == w.categories.last) ? "#{c}" : "#{c}, " 
        %p.description
          = w.description
        - if w.link.present?
          .link{:class => ("not_alone" if w.code.present?)}
            %a{href:"#{w.link}"}
              %span.text
                link
              %span.arrow
                >
        - if w.code.present?
          .code
            %a{href:"#{w.code}"}
              %span.text
                code
              %span.arrow
                >

